# tests/replay/.bless-audit.log
# Append-only audit log for the M04 replay-gate `--bless` flow.
# Format (tab-separated, one entry per line, terminated by `\n`):
#   <iso8601-utc>\t<user_name> <<user_email>>\t<branch>\t<sha>\t<fixture_path>\t<reason>
# Lines beginning with `#` are reserved as header comments. The CHIO_BLESS
# gate (see `tests/replay/src/bless.rs`) is the only sanctioned writer.
# Source-of-truth: `.planning/trajectory/04-deterministic-replay.md`,
# section "CHIO_BLESS gate logic", clause 7.
#
# `<sha>` discipline: at bless time the staged audit line, goldens, and
# (optionally) `docs/replay-compat.md` are not yet committed, so the
# bless flow writes the placeholder `<commit-sha-pending>` into the
# `<sha>` column. After the bless commit lands (typically the squash-
# merge SHA of the corresponding PR), run `scripts/seal-bless-audit.sh`
# to rewrite the placeholder rows in this file to the real SHA on a
# follow-up commit. Sealing is operator-initiated rather than tied to
# a `post-commit` hook so each audit row records exactly one commit.
